to the C64"


µJLµF1µC0Ghandy:µC3 You have obviously never published anything on the C64, how come? Is the connection to that scene missing, or what's the reason?

µC0Critikill:µC4 I never warmed to the C64 and I have not emotional connection, so I never had the reason to dive into this special and separated scene.

My heart has always beaten for Amiga and still does. I don't like to hear SIDs, I am not a fan of the C64 palette and double pixels. Visual expressions means to me that I also have the possibility to choose colours that match my pixel theme and support the pixel artwork. Just to do an artwork or demo just because of restrictions isn't the way I go.
µC0Ghandy:µC3 How come you didn't leave the scene, unlike many other graphic artists? Maybe because you are active on several platforms? Or was it a matter of friendship?

µC0Critikill:µC4 I only left for short periods 5 years, 10 years and always found back because of friendship. The scene community always was great.

And after every comeback I discovered new interesting things. Pushing pixels for 16 bit home computers for example I really rediscovered and started new in 2020, when covid started. I had time in home office and got deeper into the pixel scene because of the weekly compose at µC7pixeljoint.comµC4. From this moment on the pixels have grabbed me again.


µF0µC1Interested in typography and urban artµC0µF1

